en feel that crushing ache when you realized you could never pull them back.\n\n- Dan Krokos, The Planet Thieves\n|\nWhat if my greatest disappointments, or the aching of this life, is the revealing of a greater thirst this world can't satisfy?\n\n- Laura\n|\nWhat separates people who made their dreams come true is not setting goals to achieve a life the way they expect it to be, but how they expect to be, in order to achieve it.\n\n- Shannon\n|\nSometimes it isn't easy to be sane, smart, and responsible. Sometimes it sucks. Sucks wang. Camel wang. But that doesn't turn wrong into right or stupid into smart.\n\n- Jim Butcher, Cold Days\n|\nI started to find out the path to the HELL in a decent way. Then I realized that now it's been called SOCIETY, and I'm already part of it.\n\n- Balakoteswara\n|\nSociety can be a bitch.''And is by no means always right. Society can't know you like you know yourself. So don't let society be the judge of your actions. Only you can judge you.\n\n- G.B. Gordon, When to Hold Them\n|\nTattoos, after all, are a passionate, usually doomed assertion of mastery of your own destiny, or at least a defiant embrace of one that you cannot control.\n\n- Mark Simpson, Saint Morrissey: A Portrait of This Charming Man by an Alarming Fan\n|\nPeace shouldn't be an option, it must be the objective, peace shouldn't be a possibility, it must be the purpose.\n\n- Amit\n|\nBillions of years before I was born I did not need religion, why should I need it, billions of years after I cease to exist\n\n- Bangambiki Habyarimana, The Great Pearl of Wisdom\n|\nI'm afraid, based on my own experience, that fascism will come to America in the name of national security.\n\n- Jim\n|\nPraise is a very used, but always new, of surrendering to vanity\n\n- José\n|\nIf you truly love someone, he or she will inevitably love you back. If you find yourself in an emotional one way street, walk away! Trust that it’s not love.\n\n- Stefan\n|\nChange is a friend to a life with a vision, but an enemy to an aimless person.\n\n- Innocent Mwatsikesimbe, The Vision\n|\nWe are soon approaching a refined holiday, 'Merry Mas,' where Christ will be taken out of its context.\n\n- Anthony\n|\nGoodness, armed with power, is corrupted; and pure love without power is destroyed.\n\n- Reinhold\n|\nCall on the Saviour, He will save you.\n\n- Lailah\n|\nOne moment the world is as it is. The next, it is something entirely different. Something it has never been before.\n\n- Anne Rice, Pandora\n|\nWhen you love God for real, you will love His creation\n\n- Sunday\n|\nShe turned back to the reporter, holding out the microphone. “I'm not an expert, I'm a survivor. I hope you can learn how to be one yourself.\n\n- Rose Wynters, Phase One: Identify\n|\nIn a war, you wield every weapon you have, including words. Especially words.\n\n- Fonda Lee, Exo\n|\nDon't, Sir, accustom yourself to use big words for little matters.\n\n- Samuel Johnson, The Life of Samuel Johnson, Vol 2\n|\nA man might engage in flirtation with distinterest, even disdain. But he never teases without affection.\n\n- Tessa Dare, A Week to Be Wicked\n|\nNothing is impossible, Everything should be possible when we trying for achieve the goal\n\n- Sanjeev\n|\nBe happy when you work, thankful when you earn, cautious when you spend, shrewd when you save, and charitable when you give.\n\n- Matshona\n|\nPeople never lie so much as after a hunt, during a war, or before an election.\n\n- Otto\n|\nThe ink was secret nectar, for Marin isn't married.\n\n- Jessie Burton, The Miniaturist\n|\nLincoln learned to summon the passions, but he never addressed his audience as sweethearts.\n\n- Richard Brookhiser, Founders' Son: A Life of Abraham Lincoln\n|\nAll reality about me now appeared to be in tatters, taken down and reduced to the civil war of its particles. I held on very, very tight indeed.\n\n- Sebastian Faulks, Engleby\n|\nI love healthy stuff and junk an equal amount. Whatever I'm craving, I go for it. I'm n